caption: Got the Cali Love wrap and was disappointed at how bland it tasted. If I'm paying $14 for a wrap, I'd like for it to be flavorful which you can achieve that and still be healthy. Maybe there are other options that are tasty but it's not worth the price to find out.

Left Coast was really tasty! Decided to go here because I wanted a healthier option for lunch. I got the “CALIFORNIA LOVE” wrap which has chicken breast, black beans, brown rice, romaine, red onion, roasted tomato salsa, avocado, tahini-yogurt, whole grain wrap. I loved this wrap! It was great! It is on a bed of salad also which I loved! I also split with my friend a “ROBUST ROSA” salad which had kale, spinach, roasted broccoli, red onion, roasted tomato, toasted hemp seeds, avocado caesar dressing. It was tasty. The hemp seeds add an extra element to the salad. The prices are a little high but it was good the food!

ALLERGY HAZARD: despite their diet-friendly options, they are not prepared to handle anaphylactic allergies. They don’t know what’s in their food, and don’t particularly care if that harms someone.  The meal was ordered specifically sesame-free, and that note was sent to the chef. When the food came out, they assured it was allergen free. It actually contained tahini (sesame paste) and caused an anaphylactic reaction sending my friend immediately to the hospital.  They tried to offer her more food - and insulting lack of understanding about what happens when you feed someone with allergies a food that can kill them while telling them it’s safe.

DO NOT COME HERE IF YOU HAVE FOOD ALLERGIES. The staff has no idea what ingredients are in the food and is ill equipped to check. I suffered from an anaphylactic reaction after visiting the N Lincoln Ave location. I notified the cashier of my allergies before ordering and asked him to confirm before placing my order with the chef. Then, after eating multiple bites of food I realized my mouth and throat were itching. I returned my meal to the kitchen and was then informed that the meal actually did contain my allergen. They offered to void my order but did not show remorse or take the situation very seriously. They were surprised that I was on my way to the hospital and did not want to order something else. This restaurant put my life at risk today, and I will never be back.

Couldn’t have received worse service after I ordered two açaí bowls through caviar tonight. They took over two hours to be delivered and when the did they were completely inedible. A soupy melted mess that spilled all over the bag they were being delivered. Then called the restaurant to discuss the poor service and they put me on hold for over 15 minutes until I hung up and tried to call back but the phone number would go straight to a full voicemail. Very poor service which is disappointing since I’ve ordered the same thing a few weeks ago and they were amazing.
